From 1f110e06893af3b5255986668ae37de23c1d809d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dfattal <dfattal@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 26 Jun 2026 03:29:28 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 04/40] [displayxr inline-3d #625 B2c.1] GPU-thread synthetic
 weave pipe + Viz substitution
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Wire the full B2c.1 pipe: a synthetic side-by-side input woven via the real
xrWeaveSubmitEXT and substituted for the canvas quad in Viz, all driven from the
GPU thread (SkiaOutputSurfaceImplOnGpu) — the same thread the B2b Mojo remote is
bound on. (Design: docs/roadmap/webxr-step-b-design.md §7.)

Pipe (validated firing end-to-end on Leia):
- mojom: WeaveSubmit(DXGIHandle texture, Rect) => (DisplayXRWeaveResult? {woven,
  fence, fence_value, w/h, eyes}) — [Sync], win-gated.
- Browser DisplayXRWeaverImpl drives the real xrWeaveSubmitEXT on the B2a
  present-owner session (DisplayXRWeaveClient::Submit, OpenXR-free facade) and
  returns the woven texture/fence/eyes.
- GPU DisplayXRWeaveGpu (impl of new viz::DisplayXRWeaveProvider): owns the Mojo
  remote + a keyed-mutex synthetic SBS input (left=red/right=blue test pattern on
  its own D3D11 device), drives the [Sync] weave, hands woven handles to Viz.
  Registered process-globally in ShellContentGpuClient::PostCompositorThreadCreated.
- Viz: SkiaRenderer tags the canvas TextureDrawQuad (ExternalUseClient::
  ImageContext::set_weave_target); SkiaOutputSurfaceImplOnGpu::MaybeWeaveSubstitute
  (both Ganesh + Graphite paths) calls the provider, imports the woven handle as a
  SharedImage (D3DImageBackingFactory), GPU-waits the fence (D3DSharedFence), and
  redirects the tagged ImageContextImpl to the woven backing via an override
  mailbox (size check relaxed; woven is window-sized).
- Forward --enable-inline-3d to child processes so the GPU/Viz process registers
  the provider + tags the quad.

Validated on Leia (content_shell --enable-inline-3d, with
--disable-direct-composition so Viz draws quads via SkiaRenderer rather than
delegating them to DComp visuals): DrawTextureQuad tags the canvas → provider
found → synthetic SBS input created → Mojo [Sync] → browser → real
xrWeaveSubmitEXT called with a valid NT handle + window-relative rect. Both
content_shell and the service confirmed High integrity (handle dup OK).

KNOWN BLOCKER (runtime-side, not this patch): xrWeaveSubmitEXT returns -2
(XR_ERROR_RUNTIME_FAILURE) — comp_d3d11_service_weave_submit hits a silent
early-return (no service-side log reached: no OpenSharedResource / "server
output"). The browser passes a valid handle, so the import/fence/substitute path
is not yet exercised. Pinpointing needs a service-side entry log (runtime
rebuild). The null-DACL on the synthetic input's CreateSharedHandle (so the
external service can open a sandboxed-GPU-created handle) is a precaution for the
B2c.2 canvas export; it did not change the -2 and is unverified.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
